<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1146,1892]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,1786,1812]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</emphasis>
Apparently, 
<taxonomicName box="[516,630,1787,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Paradelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctica">
<emphasis box="[516,630,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
replaces 
<taxonomicName authority="Ringdahl, 1959" authorityName="Ringdahl" authorityYear="1959" box="[746,894,1787,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pseudonupedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intersecta">
<emphasis box="[746,894,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">P. intersecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above the tree line in all arctic and elevated northern landmasses of Eurasia and North 
<collectingCountry box="[648,752,1826,1852]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">America</collectingCountry>
, but data are currently lacking for many parts of the Palaearctic Region including 
<collectingCountry box="[433,515,1866,1892]" name="Russia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
